        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 11:57AM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 1156 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Peoria, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mossville, Spring Bay, West Peoria, Alta, Bellevue, Washington,
Norwood, Rome, Dunlap, Peoria, Peoria Heights, Bay View Gardens,
Metamora, Germantown Hills, East Peoria, Morton, Edelstein, and Creve
Coeur.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 155 near mile marker 31.
Interstate 474 between mile markers 0 and 5, and between mile
markers 13 and 14.
Interstate 74 between mile markers 83 and 102.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
